<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="uncomfortable-adj">uncomfortable <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʌn'kʌmftəbl, ʌn'kʌmfətəbl/    美 /ʌn'kʌmftəbl, ʌn'kʌmfərtəbl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(人) 不舒服的；不安的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Having taken a drink, I felt rather uncomfortable and got a headache. 
喝了一杯酒后，我感觉非常不舒服，而且还头疼。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I feel uncomfortable with strangers.
我和陌生人在一起时会感到不自在。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(物) 令人不舒服的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an uncomfortable chair
令人不舒服的椅子</p></div></div>